1
00:00:11,010 --> 00:00:13,720
Ugh, I don't get this at all.

2
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:17,480
Ah, look here.
Your limits of integration are reversed.

3
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:18,640
Huh? Where?

4
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:22,520
You need to find the x-intercepts
first.

5
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,860
Oh, I see.

6
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:27,110
If you don't do it step-by-step,
everything after will be wrong.

7
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:28,360
So pay close attention.

8
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:32,410
Oh, brother dear,
thank you so much!

9
00:00:32,410 --> 00:00:34,030
Now I can definitely
survive this.

10
00:00:35,540 --> 00:00:37,250
Whoa, hold on.

11
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:39,580
That's so embarrassing.
Stop it.

12
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:57,180
Students and working adults
have completely different values.

13
00:00:57,180 --> 00:01:00,310
Waiting for someone to come home
can be exhausting, too.

14
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:14,700
I guess so.
